<section class="problem section" id="problem">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="problem__text">
      <h2 class="problem__heading">By the Time You Know, It's Already Cost You</h2>

      <p>A missing tooth enters a crusher. A buried drill rod is scooped into a haul truck. A boulder too large for the grizzly hits the feed.</p>

      <p>By the time someone spots it — if they spot it at all — the damage is done. Crushed components. Torn conveyor belts. Unplanned downtime costing hundreds of thousands, sometimes millions.</p>

      <p>Most mining operations still rely on manual visual checks or sensors placed too far downstream to prevent the problem. The harsh reality of remote, dusty, high-temperature sites has kept advanced computer vision out of reach — and the teams capable of building it have been drawn to autonomous vehicles and robotics, not mining.</p>

      <p class="problem__kicker">The result: billions of pounds of equipment operating with almost no intelligent oversight at the point of operation, where it matters most.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="problem__images">
      <div class="problem__image-panel">
        <p class="problem__image-label">Consequence — damaged crusher or torn conveyor belt</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem__image-panel">
        <p class="problem__image-label">Environment — excavator mid-dig in harsh, dusty conditions</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

